1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,800
Some species punch above their weight — remove them and ecosystems unravel.

2
00:00:04,800 --> 00:00:08,800
These are called keystone species, vital to their habitats’ health.

3
00:00:08,800 --> 00:00:14,000
Take the sea otter; without it, urchin populations explode and kelp forests vanish.

4
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:16,000
Or consider wolves in Yellowstone.

5
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:19,200
Their presence balances elk populations, promoting plant diversity.

6
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:23,600
Removing keystone species can lead to domino effects, collapsing entire ecosystems.

7
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:26,000
But it’s not just about animals.

8
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:28,000
Plants can be keystone too.

9
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:31,600
Think of the mighty fig tree, supporting countless species.

10
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:33,600
Curious about more ecological wonders?

11
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:35,200
Hit that follow button!
